{"aid": "http://arxiv.org/abs/2503.23936v1", "title": "On stable Kim-forking and rosy theories", "summary": "We provide a partial answer to a question asked independently by Kim and
d'Elb\'ee and show that, under the assumption of the stable Kim-forking
conjecture, every $\mathrm{NSOP}_1$ rosy theory must be simple. We also prove
that the theory of a Frobenius field has stable Kim-forking.", "main_category": "math.LO", "categories": "math.LO", "published": "2025-03-31T10:34:59Z"}
